---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";

const lastUpdated = "June 1, 2026";
---

<Base
  title="Gissa — Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy policy for Gissa, a party game by Fjord Labs."
  noindex={true}
>
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-8">
        <img
          src="/images/fjordlabsicon.png"
          alt="Gissa"
          class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full"
        />
        <div>
          <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-heading font-bold text-bark">
            Gissa — Privacy Policy
          </h1>
          <p class="text-sm text-bark/50">Operated by Fjord Labs</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-sm text-bark/40 mb-8">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

      <div class="prose-article">
        <p>
          This Privacy Policy explains how <strong>Gissa</strong> (“Gissa”, “the
          app”, “we”, “us”), a party game operated by Fjord Labs, handles your
          information. We designed Gissa to be privacy-friendly: the core game
          is fully playable as a guest, offline, without an account. By using
          Gissa you agree to the practices described below.
        </p>

        <h2>1. Play without an account</h2>
        <p>
          You can play Gissa without signing in. In guest mode the game runs
          locally on your device and we do not collect personal information
          about you. Creating an account is optional and unlocks cloud sync,
          game history, and premium features.
        </p>

        <h2>2. Information we collect</h2>
        <p>We collect only what is needed to provide the features you use:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Account information.</strong> If you sign in with Email,
            Apple, or Google, we receive an account identifier and (depending on
            the method) your email address. Authentication is handled by our
            backend provider, Supabase. We use Sign in with Apple's
            private-relay email when you choose to hide your address.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Your content.</strong> When signed in, the decks you create
            with the AI generator and your game history are stored in your
            account so they sync across devices.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Purchase information.</strong> If you buy a subscription or
            credit pack, our payments provider, RevenueCat, processes the
            transaction and stores your subscription status and transaction
            identifiers. We never receive or store your full payment-card
            details — those are handled entirely by Apple.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>AI deck topics.</strong> When you use the “make any deck”
            feature, the topic text you enter is sent to our server and to
            Anthropic (the Claude API) to generate the deck. Don't include
            personal or sensitive information in deck topics.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Language &amp; settings.</strong> Your chosen language and
            app preferences are stored locally on your device.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>3. Camera and the reaction reel</h2>
        <p>
          Gissa includes an optional “reaction reel” that uses your device's
          <strong>front camera</strong> to record the final few seconds of a
          round so you can play it back and share it. Key points:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            The camera is used <strong>only</strong> while a game is in progress,
            with your permission.
          </li>
          <li>
            Reaction clips are kept
            <strong>on your device for the current session only</strong> and are
            <strong>not uploaded to our servers</strong>.
          </li>
          <li>
            The recording captures
            <strong>video only — no microphone audio</strong> is recorded.
          </li>
          <li>
            A clip leaves your device only if <em>you</em> choose to save it to
            your photo library or share it using your device's standard share
            sheet.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. How we use information</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>To provide and operate the game and its features.</li>
          <li>To authenticate you and sync your content across devices.</li>
          <li>To process and verify subscriptions and credit purchases.</li>
          <li>To generate custom decks you request through the AI feature.</li>
          <li>To maintain the security and reliability of the service.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We do <strong>not</strong> sell your personal information, and we do
          not use it for advertising.
        </p>

        <h2>5. Service providers</h2>
        <p>
          We rely on the following processors, who handle data on our behalf:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Supabase</strong> — authentication and database storage
            (accounts, custom decks, game history).
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>RevenueCat</strong> — subscription and in-app purchase
            management.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Apple</strong> — App Store payments and, if used, Sign in
            with Apple.
          </li>
          <li><strong>Google</strong> — if you choose Google sign-in.</li>
          <li>
            <strong>Anthropic (Claude API)</strong> — generating AI decks from
            the topic you enter.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>Each provider processes data under its own privacy terms.</p>

        <h2>6. Data retention</h2>
        <p>
          Account data and your synced content are retained while your account
          is active. Reaction clips are session-only and are discarded when you
          leave the game (unless you saved them yourself). You can request
          deletion of your account and associated data at any time (see “Your
          rights”).
        </p>

        <h2>7. Children's privacy</h2>
        <p>
          Gissa is a family-friendly game suitable for all ages and includes
          content intended for children. We do not knowingly collect personal
          information from children for our own purposes. Children can play in
          guest mode without an account or any data collection. Account creation
          and purchases are intended to be performed by an adult. If you believe
          a child has provided us with personal information, contact us and we
          will delete it.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Your rights</h2>
        <p>
          Depending on where you live, you may have the right to access,
          correct, export, or delete your personal information, and to withdraw
          consent. To exercise any of these rights, or to request deletion of
          your account, email us at the address below and we will respond within
          a reasonable time.
        </p>

        <h2>9. International transfers</h2>
        <p>
          Our providers may process and store data in countries other than your
          own. Where required, we rely on appropriate safeguards for such
          transfers.
        </p>

        <h2>10. Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we do, we
          will revise the “Last updated” date above. Material changes will be
          reflected here before they take effect.
        </p>

        <h2>11. Contact us</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about this policy or your data? Email
          <a href="mailto:emrah.anl@gmail.com">emrah.anl@gmail.com</a>.
        </p>

        <p class="text-sm text-bark/40 mt-12">
          Gissa is operated by Fjord Labs.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
